column6: name: First Congregational/Unitarian Church, 1820-1845 description: Chambers Street. Approximate location. Meet prior in a private house before building church. Moves to 548 Broadway in 1845. Denomination: Unitarian Date Founded/Built: 1820

name: Tabernacle Baptist Church, 1839-1850 description: Move to same block as NY Historical Society in 1850. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1839

name: Welsh Presbyterian Church, 1833-1851 description: Switched from being a Congregational Church. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1833

name: Zion Protestant Episcopal Church, 1811-1852 description: Former Lutheran congregation. Worship in a small church on Mott, corner of Cross Street in 1811. It burned in 1815 when feed store across the street catches fire. They temporarily worship in the Eglise Du St Esprit until church reopens in 1818. Moved up to 38th and Madison in 1852. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1811

name: Greene Street Reformed Dutch Church, 1825-1852 description: Greene and Houston Streets. Half of schismatic congregation moved over from the Watch House on corner of Prince and Wooster Streets in 1825. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1825

name: Tenth Presbyterian Church, 1838-1852 description: Moved from rented quarters on 22nd Street near 3rd Avenue. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1838

name: Rodeph Shalom Synagogue, 1842-1852 description: Moved over to 8 Clinton Street. Denomination: Jewish Date Founded/Built: 1842

Inscription on back: "No. 15/ Infant Funeral 8 young Ladies Born by 8 young ladies/ in White followed by the Widdows & children & [Entering]/ Scene in 2d & Bayard/ now Forsyth St/ the meetinghouse ��� Engine house & Corner Store [3]/ also the Chain across the Street to prohibit the vehicles from Passing in time of Service/ Rev Doct Phoebus pastor/ 1809." Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1789
